[h4 id=Nvr 
	" NVR
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The default NVR file used is 
	[code 
		"deskpro386.nvr
	]code
	" (md5: 
	[code 
		"367072234f7095aebb4e663fb1dc8f98
	]code
	"). It can be found in the folder you installed PCem in under 
	[code 
		"/nvr/default/deskpro386.nvr
	]code
	". To be completely sure your NVR file starts off clean, take this file, copy it to 
	[code 
		"~/.pcem/nvr/
	]code
	" and name it after your config file (e.g. if your config is named late80s, name it 
	[code 
		"late80s.deskpro386.nvr
	]code
	".) If there is already a file named this, delete it and replace it.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=DiagnosticDisk 
	" Diagnostic disk
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"This chipset needs a special diagnostic disk. Without this disk, it's impossible to make important changes to the BIOS like specifying the hard drive type. It uses a common 720K disk that works across many Compaq Portable and Deskpro models, and it has an MD5 hash of 
	[code 
		"09652bd116a0af7ed006996b001ab9c9
	]code
	". You can find one yourself, or use the following instructions to make one.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"You will need 
	[code 
		"SP0308.EXE
	]code
	" (md5: 
	[code 
		"aa6991bbe7449109671508eb27630629
	]code
	") which is inside 
	[code 
		"SP0308.ZIP
	]code
	". This is the SoftPaq Diagnostics 8.00 Rev. B (DP256) utility once distributed by Compaq, which is now owned by Hewlett Packard.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[a href=ftp://ftp.hp.com/pub/softpaq/sp0000-0500/sp0308.zip rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"Download from official site
		]a
		" (
		[a href=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/sp0308.zip rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"TASVideos Mirror
		]a
		")
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[a href=ftp://ftp.hp.com/pub/softpaq/sp0000-0500/sp0308.txt rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"Official documentation
		]a
		" (
		[a href=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/sp0308.txt rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"TASVideos Mirror
		]a
		")
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Make another configuration identical to the 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=previous one|href=/EmulatorResources/PCem/DOS#Config)
	", except in the Drives tab, set FDD2 to 3.5" 2.88M and eject any hard drives.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"You will need three disks for this process.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Disk 1:
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Grab the FreeDOS v1.2 boot floppy from the 
	[a href=https://www.ibiblio.org/pub/micro/pc-stuff/freedos/files/distributions/1.2/official/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"FreeDOS website
	]a
	" in 
	[code 
		"FD12FLOPPY.zip
	]code
	". The md5 of 
	[code 
		"FLOPPY.img
	]code
	" is 
	[code 
		"36689ac4152d8efb13ab230e9aea46ec
	]code
	".
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Disk 2:
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Make a blank 1.44M floppy image and copy 
	[code 
		"SP0308.EXE
	]code
	" onto it. You can do that with the following terminal commands:
	$LF
]div
[pre 
	[code class=language-bash 
		$UNPRINTABLE TEXT!!!
	]code
]pre
[div class=p 
	"You will get inconsistent hashes for this image, but it doesn't matter.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Disk 3:
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Make a blank 720K floppy image; this will eventually be your diagnostic disk. You can make this with the following terminal command:
	$LF
]div
[pre 
	[code class=language-bash 
		$UNPRINTABLE TEXT!!!
	]code
]pre
[div class=p 
	"Again, you will get inconsistent hashes for this. This can be fixed by specifying the volume serial number with the 
	[code 
		"-i
	]code
	" parameter, but it ultimately will not matter.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Launch this new config in PCem. While the system is counting memory, with the right-click menu, change drive A: to your 
	[code 
		"FLOPPY.img
	]code
	" and change drive B: to your 
	[code 
		"sp0308.img
	]code
	". You will get some error after the memory is done counting, press F1 to resume and the computer should boot using the FreeDOS floppy.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"FreeDOS setup will start, but we don't need to install it. Select 
	[code 
		"English
	]code
	" as the language and then select 
	[code 
		"No - Return to DOS
	]code
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This will take you out to the DOS prompt. Type 
	[code 
		"B:
	]code
	" and press enter to go to the B drive. Use the right click menu to swap drive A to 
	[code 
		"compaqdd.img
	]code
	", the blank 720K disk. B has the setup program on it, so type 
	[code 
		"SP0308
	]code
	" into the prompt and press enter.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The setup program will bring up some legal warnings, press enter, PgDn through the license agreement, then enter "AGREED" into the box at the end.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The setup utility made some new files on the B drive, namely 
	[code 
		"QRST.EXE
	]code
	". In the DOS prompt, type 
	[code 
		"QRST
	]code
	" and press enter.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The new program will ask what type of transfer you want, select 
	[code 
		"All diskettes in the set
	]code
	" (there is only one anyway). It will ask for a blank 720K disk, which you should already have in the A drive, so press enter twice.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Wait for the program to finish writing the disk. When it's done, it will kick you back out to the DOS prompt. Close PCem.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[code 
		"compaqdd.img
	]code
	" should now be a working diagnostic disk. Check the hash of it, it should have an MD5 of 
	[code 
		"09652bd116a0af7ed006996b001ab9c9
	]code
	". If it doesn't match the hash exactly, it may still work fine.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=LibtasMovieFile 
	" libTAS movie file
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"At this point, you can run the verification movie if you want our exact hashes:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	(__wikiLink|href=/Userfiles/Info/73801777262948657|implicitdisplaytext=Userfiles/Info/73801777262948657)
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Bios 
	" BIOS
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Launch the config (the original one, NOT the one for the diagnostic disk) and wait for the memory test to complete. When prompted, load the diagnostic disk image into drive A: and press F1. You will see a memory test error, this is normal.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/memory-test-error.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"On the screen with the Compaq logo, Press Enter to continue setup. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/compaq-logo.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"There will be another memory size error screen, press Enter. Put in any valid date and press Enter (libTAS will override this). It will then tell you your configuration was updated, press Enter again.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"After reaching the "System Configuration Summary" screen, press F4 to Change Configuration.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/system-configuration-summary-change-configuration.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Select the Fixed Disk Drives option and press Enter. Select "Other Type" for Disk Controller 1, Fixed Disk 1 and press Enter.
	$LF
	"Type in 09 for the drive type and press Enter.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/system-configuration-summary-fixed-disk-drive.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Set Disk Controller 1, Fixed Disk 2 and Disk Controller 2, Fixed Disk 1 to type 0.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Back at the Change Configuration menu, select NumLock Power-On State and press Enter. Change it to On and press Enter.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Press Esc to close the Change Configuration window.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Note that both disk drives are set to 1.44 MB (3.5"). For drive B:, this is not correct, but the 5.25-inch choices cause boot errors, possibly a problem with PCem. Drive B: will be able to read 5.25 inch disks regardless of this choice.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Press F3, then select Exit and save changes.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The PC will restart and look for bootable media.  Eject the diagnostic disk from drive A: and proceed to the 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=FreeDOS Installation section|href=/EmulatorResources/PCem/DOS#FreedosInstallation)
	".
	$LF
]div
