[h4 id=Bios_2 
	" BIOS
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Launch the config and wait a while - the system needs to reconfigure itself. Eventually, you will see this screen:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/nvram-checksum-error.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This is normal, it's just a warning that something changed in the system. Press F1 to load setup. Press F5 to load the setup defaults and press enter - this ensures the NVR starts from a clean slate.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/load-setup-defaults.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Back on the setup screen, select Floppy Options and press enter.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/floppy-options.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"On the Floppy Options screen, set the drives to what they were in the config: A: is a 3.5" 2.88 MB and B: is 5.25" 1.2 MB.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/floppy-b-type.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Press Esc to back out to the main setup screen. Now select Boot Options and press enter.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/boot-options.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Set the boot order so that the First Boot Device is CD-ROM. Disable the rest for now. Remember how to do this - you will need to change this again later! Press F10 to save and exit.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/dos/configurations/first-boot-device.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The PC will restart looking for bootable media: proceed to the 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=FreeDOS Installation section|href=/EmulatorResources/PCem/DOS#FreedosInstallation)
	".
	$LF
]div
